@node Description "DESCRIPTION:"

DESCRIPTION
-----------
This program is designed to make programs in your toolsdaemon (or whatever)
program easier to use by providing an automatic filerequester for cli
commands placed there.

And it's my first C program too!
(and the main part of the source code's only about 4 lines long)
@endnode

@node Requirements "REQUIREMENTS:"

REQUIREMENTS
------------
An Amiga running kickstart 2.x+, and a requestfile command somewhere
in your path.
(And about 5K free)

If you have 3.x, you already have the command.
If you have 2.x, there is a clone of requestfile on Aminet, or
if you have some install disk with some 3.x stuff on it, the 3.x
requestfile command will work.
@endnode

@node Usage
USAGE
-----
The best place to use this is from one of those tools-daemon-like programs
(or the real thing)
examples I give here are for toolsdaemon.

Go into toolsprefs, and let's say...you'd like to put memacs into a 
menu item.

Add the item, and go to the commands listview.
Select Add.
Insert the following:
memacs `addfreq []`

Hit return.
Set the cyclegadget from WB to CLI.
save & exit.

Now if you want to edit a file with memacs, you will have a filerequester
come up if you do not select an icon.

Other programs like textviewers, pic viewers, decrunchers, etc...
can be made more useful with this.

Example #2
(my favorite...due to laziness)
Adding a RUN item to a toolsdaemon menu...
The command is:
wbrun `addfreq []`

This is really nice if you want to run something buried 300 drawers
deep on workbench and you don't feel like opening them all up!

Yes, I'm using the backwards single-quote to redirect the output of
the program to be used as input to the program in front of it.
..Just like good ol' unix!
(yesss...it works the same on AmigaOS)

@endnode


